Body:
BRD reviewed with submitter, added additional details that did not pull over from Ivanti (below) regarding scope of this request being for all ambulatory, and not limited to Urgent as original request stated, Smart phrase below had been drafted in attempt to have easily accessible SDEs for this reporting:

 
By: Ciara Smith (C350735)Sent: a year ago
Met with the requestors and Tiffany Smith around this request. Currently, All ambulatory practices and urgent cares are tracking transfers from their outpatient sites to the ED with Safe Connect. Safe Connect is not a reliable way to record this information and they have been asked to find an alternative. Currently there are three identified ways a patient gets sent to the ED from the ambulatory space
1.    From urgent care, they are told to go to the ED (private vs ambulance)
2.    From outpatient setting they are told to go to the ED (private vs ambulance)
3.    Triage nurse on the phone tells patient to go to the ED

To measure these events for regulatory requirements- the group discussed with Krista and I the ability to have a smart phrase with data elements to capture these transfers in care connect. The group previously have drafted what they would like this smart phrase to look like.

.EmergencyTX
This individual suffers from an emergency medical condition that requires care beyond our services provided. After clinical assessment by \{PROVIDER/CLINICIAN NAME} it has been determined this patient requires emergency medical care or/transfer to higher level of care.
Explanation of benefits of transfer and risks of refusing transfer: YES/NO
Agreeable to Transfer: YES/NO
Transferred to: \{NAME}
Mode of Transportation: \{EMS/PRIVATE VEHICLE/MEDICAL CAB/UBER/BUS/WALK/FREETEXT}
Report to:
Family/Agency: \{NAME}
EMS: \{NAME}
EMS Arrival Time: \{0000}
Transfer Center Contacted: \{NAME}
Refuses Transfer: YES/NO
Accompanied by: \{NAME/FREETEXT}
Mode of Transportation: \{PRIVATE VEHICLE/WALK/MEDICAL CAB/UBER/BUS/FREETEXT}
Notifications: \{PROVIDER/SECURITY/SW/911}
Reported Reason: \{FREETEXT – why transfer is refused}
Interpretation Provided: YES/NO
Language:
Name or ID#:
With this smartphrase, can we include the ability to include a discrete data element so we can report on and measure how often these events occur?
